[optional body: explain what changed and why]

[optional footer(s)]

# Conventional Commits 1.0.0 shape:
#   <type>[optional scope][optional !]: <description>
#   [optional body]
#   [optional footer(s)]
#
# Repository types:
#   feat      new user-facing or API behavior
#   fix       bug fix
#   docs      documentation-only change
#   test      test, benchmark, or manual-regression harness change
#   refactor  internal code change with no behavior change
#   chore     repository maintenance
#   build     build, dependency, or tooling change
#   ci        CI or release automation change
#   perf      performance improvement
#   style     formatting-only change
#   revert    revert a previous commit
#
# Breaking changes are disallowed while ROADMAP.md says so.
# Use ! or a BREAKING CHANGE: footer only when the repo's breaking-change policy permits it.
#
# Examples:
#   feat(books): add publication-year search filter
#   fix(security): reject forged csrf headers
#   docs: update manual regression workflow
#   test(manual-regression): add execution log example report
